SIMPLE: preoccupate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preoccupate
<hw>Pre*oc"cu*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praeoccupatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praeoccupare</ets> to preoccupy.
See <er>Preoccupy</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To anticipate; to take before.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Fear <xex>preoccupateth</xex> it
[death].⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To prepossess; to prejudice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preoccupation</ent>⟦br⟧
